# AXI Protocol — UVC Development & Verification

A UVM-based Universal Verification Component (UVC) built from scratch to verify
AXI protocol behavior independently of the DUT (Design Under Test).

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- Language: SystemVerilog
- Methodology: UVM (Universal Verification Methodology)
- Assertions: SVA (SystemVerilog Assertions)

## ✨ Features
- Modular UVM environment (Agent, Driver, Monitor, Scoreboard, Sequencer)
- Verified five-channel AXI handshaking (AW, W, B, AR, R)
- Write data interleaving across multiple burst types (FIXED, INCR, WRAP)
- SVA integration for real-time bus compliance monitoring
- Detects timing violations and data integrity issues across all channels

## 📂 Project Structure
├── tb/               # Testbench top
├── env/              # UVM Environment
├── agent/            # Driver, Monitor, Sequencer
├── sequences/        # Test sequences
├── assertions/       # SVA properties
└── tests/            # UVM test classes

## ⚙️ How to Run
```bash
# Example with QuestaSim / ModelSim
vlog -sv tb/top.sv
vsim -c top -do "run -all"
```

